!Sample_data_processing	"Trimmed reads were aligned to human (GRCh38) genome reference using STAR (v.2.7.3a; parameters: --twopassMode Basic --outSAMmapqUnique 60 --sjdbGTFfile) with splice junctions from the human GENCODE annotation (release 35). To eliminate residual contamination from mouse RNA, reads derived from xenograft models were also aligned to mouse (GRCm38) genome reference using STAR (v.2.7.3a; parameters: --twopassMode Basic --outSAMmapqUnique 60 --sjdbGTFfile) , with splice junctions from the mouse GENCODE annotation (release M25), and assigned to either human or mouse using Disambiguate (v1.0.0)."	"Trimmed reads were aligned to human (GRCh38) genome reference using STAR (v.2.7.3a; parameters: --twopassMode Basic --outSAMmapqUnique 60 --sjdbGTFfile) with splice junctions from the human GENCODE annotation (release 35). To eliminate residual contamination from mouse RNA, reads derived from xenograft models were also aligned to mouse (GRCm38) genome reference using STAR (v.2.7.3a; parameters: --twopassMode Basic --outSAMmapqUnique 60 --sjdbGTFfile) , with splice junctions from the mouse GENCODE annotation (release M25), and assigned to either human or mouse using Disambiguate (v1.0.0)."	"Trimmed reads were aligned to human (GRCh38) genome reference using STAR (v.2.7.3a; parameters: --twopassMode Basic --outSAMmapqUnique 60 --sjdbGTFfile) with splice junctions from the human GENCODE annotation (release 35). To eliminate residual contamination from mouse RNA, reads derived from xenograft models were also aligned to mouse (GRCm38) genome reference using STAR (v.2.7.3a; parameters: --twopassMode Basic --outSAMmapqUnique 60 --sjdbGTFfile) , with splice junctions from the mouse GENCODE annotation (release M25), and assigned to either human or mouse using Disambiguate (v1.0.0)."	"Trimmed reads were aligned to human (GRCh38) genome reference using STAR (v.2.7.3a; parameters: --twopassMode Basic --outSAMmapqUnique 60 --sjdbGTFfile) with splice junctions from the 